{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779168258674,"sessionID":"ses_1c14f16cdffegT7S1cr6CAFB7m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_ciKP1BnLJvF2WAYLPZ5r3064","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PROJECT_DATABASE\n2: \n3: ## Schema Overview\n4: \n5: All entities extend `BaseEntity` which provides:\n6: - `id` — UUID primary key\n7: - `createdAt` — `timestamp` (auto-managed)\n8: - `updatedAt` — `timestamp` (auto-managed)\n9: - `deletedAt` — `timestamp | null` (soft delete support)\n10: \n11: Column naming convention: `snake_case` in the database (`@CreateDateColumn({ name: 'created_at' })`).\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Entities\n16: \n17: ### User\n18: \n19: Represents all registered users (Renters and Admins). Extends `BaseEntity` with soft delete.\n20: \n21: **Table:** `users`\n22: \n23: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n24: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n25: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n26: | `name` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | User's full name |\n27: | `email` | `varchar(255)` | UNIQUE, NOT NULL | Login email address |\n28: | `password` | `varchar(255)` | NOT NULL | bcrypt-hashed password |\n29: | `phone` | `varchar(20)` | NULLABLE | Optional phone number |\n30: | `role` | `enum` (`RoleEnum`) | NOT NULL, default: `'renter'` | `renter` \\| `admin` |\n31: | `status` | `enum` (`UserStatusEnum`) | NOT NULL, default: `'active'` | `active` \\| `suspended` |\n32: | `email_verified_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Null until email verification completes |\n33: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n34: | `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n35: | `deleted_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Soft delete timestamp |\n36: \n37: **Indexes:**\n38: - `UNIQUE` on `email`\n39: - `INDEX` on `role`\n40: - `INDEX` on `status`\n41: - `INDEX` on `(role, status)` composite\n42: \n43: **Relationships:**\n44: - `hasMany` → `RefreshToken` (one user has many refresh tokens)\n45: - `hasMany` → `PasswordResetToken` (one user has many reset tokens)\n46: - `hasMany` → `Favorite` (one user has many favorites)\n47: - `hasMany` → `Inquiry` (one user submits many inquiries)\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### RefreshToken\n52: \n53: Stores JWT refresh tokens for rotation and invalidation. Each refresh creates a new row; the old row is marked deleted when rotated. Not extending `BaseEntity` (no need for update timestamps or soft delete — expiries handle lifecycle).\n54: \n55: **Table:** `refresh_tokens`\n56: \n57: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n58: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n59: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Primary key |\n60: | `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Owning user |\n61: | `token` | `varchar(500)` | NOT NULL, UNIQUE | Encoded JWT refresh token string |\n62: | `expires_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL | Token expiration time (7 days from issue) |\n63: | `revoked_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Set when token is rotated or user logs out |\n64: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Token creation time |\n65: \n66: **Indexes:**\n67: - `UNIQUE` on `token`\n68: - `INDEX` on `user_id`\n69: - `INDEX` on `expires_at`\n70: \n71: **Relationships:**\n72: - `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ### PasswordResetToken\n77: \n78: Stores tokens for the forgot-password / reset-password flow. Tokens expire after a configurable window (e.g., 1 hour).\n79: \n80: **Table:** `password_reset_tokens`\n81: \n82: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n83: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n84: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Primary key |\n85: | `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Owning user |\n86: | `token` | `varchar(500)` | NOT NULL, UNIQUE | Secure random reset token |\n87: | `expires_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL | Token expiry (e.g., 1 hour from creation) |\n88: | `used_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Set when password is successfully reset |\n89: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Token creation time |\n90: \n91: **Indexes:**\n92: - `UNIQUE` on `token`\n93: - `INDEX` on `user_id`\n94: \n95: **Relationships:**\n96: - `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ### Property\n101: \n102: Represents a rental property listing. Supports soft delete (archiving). Address fields are stored as individual columns for search/indexing; API layer nests them into an `address` object.\n103: \n104: **Table:** `properties`\n105: \n106: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n107: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n108: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n109: | `title` | `varchar(200)` | NOT NULL | Listing title (5–200 chars) |\n110: | `description` | `text` | NOT NULL | Full description (20–5000 chars) |\n111: | `price` | `decimal(10,2)` | NOT NULL | Monthly rent (> 0) |\n112: | `bedrooms` | `integer` | NOT NULL, CHECK (≥ 0) | Number of bedrooms |\n113: | `bathrooms` | `integer` | NOT NULL, CHECK (≥ 0) | Number of bathrooms |\n114: | `square_feet` | `integer` | NULLABLE, CHECK (> 0) | Living area in square feet |\n115: | `property_type` | `enum` (`PropertyTypeEnum`) | NOT NULL | `apartment` \\| `house` \\| `condo` \\| `townhouse` \\| `studio` |\n116: | `address_street` | `varchar(200)` | NOT NULL | Street address |\n117: | `address_city` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | City |\n118: | `address_state` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | State / province |\n119: | `address_zip_code` | `varchar(10)` | NOT NULL | ZIP / postal code |\n120: | `address_latitude` | `decimal(10,7)` | NULLABLE | Geocoordinate latitude (-90 to 90) |\n121: | `address_longitude` | `decimal(10,7)` | NULLABLE | Geocoordinate longitude (-180 to 180) |\n122: | `available_from` | `date` | NULLABLE | Date property becomes available |\n123: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n124: | `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n125: | `deleted_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Soft delete / archive timestamp |\n126: \n127: **Indexes:**\n128: - `INDEX` on `property_type`\n129: - `INDEX` on `price`\n130: - `INDEX` on `bedrooms`\n131: - `INDEX` on `bathrooms`\n132: - `INDEX` on `address_city`\n133: - `INDEX` on `address_state`\n134: - `INDEX` on `(address_latitude, address_longitude)` — geospatial queries\n135: - `GIN INDEX` or `tsvector` on `title || ' ' || description || ' ' || address_city || ' ' || address_state` for full-text search (optional, for performance at scale)\n136: \n137: **Relationships:**\n138: - `hasMany` → `PropertyPhoto` (one property has many photos)\n139: - `belongsToMany` → `Amenity` via `property_amenities` junction\n140: - `hasMany` → `Favorite` (one property is favorited by many users)\n141: - `hasMany` → `Inquiry` (one property receives many inquiries)\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: ### PropertyPhoto\n146: \n147: Stores uploaded photos for a property. Multiple photos per property with ordering and a primary photo designation.\n148: \n149: **Table:** `property_photos`\n150: \n151: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n152: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n153: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n154: | `property_id` | `uuid` | FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Owning property |\n155: | `url` | `varchar(500)` | NOT NULL | Photo URL (S3 / CDN path) |\n156: | `is_primary` | `boolean` | NOT NULL, default: `false` | Whether this is the main/thumbnail photo |\n157: | `sort_order` | `integer` | NOT NULL, default: `0` | Display order in gallery |\n158: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n159: | `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n160: \n161: **Indexes:**\n162: - `INDEX` on `property_id`\n163: - `INDEX` on `(property_id, sort_order)`\n164: \n165: **Business Rule:** Only one photo per property may have `is_primary = true`. Enforced at the application layer.\n166: \n167: **Relationships:**\n168: - `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ### Amenity\n173: \n174: Predefined list of amenities that can be associated with properties. Managed by admins.\n175: \n176: **Table:** `amenities`\n177: \n178: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n179: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n180: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n181: | `name` | `varchar(50)` | UNIQUE, NOT NULL | Amenity name (e.g., \"parking\", \"gym\") |\n182: | `icon` | `varchar(50)` | NOT NULL | Icon identifier for frontend rendering |\n183: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n184: | `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n185: | `deleted_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Soft delete |\n186: \n187: **Indexes:**\n188: - `UNIQUE` on `name`\n189: \n190: **Relationships:**\n191: - `belongsToMany` → `Property` via `property_amenities` junction\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ### PropertyAmenity\n196: \n197: Junction table for the many-to-many relationship between `Property` and `Amenity`. Each row links one property to one amenity.\n198: \n199: **Table:** `property_amenities`\n200: \n201: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n202: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n203: | `property_id` | `uuid` | PK (composite), FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Property reference |\n204: | `amenity_id` | `uuid` | PK (composite), FK → `amenities.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Amenity reference |\n205: \n206: **Primary Key:** Composite `(property_id, amenity_id)`\n207: \n208: **Indexes:**\n209: - `INDEX` on `amenity_id`\n210: \n211: **Relationships:**\n212: - `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n213: - `belongsTo` → `Amenity` via `amenity_id`\n214: \n215: ---\n216: \n217: ### Favorite\n218: \n219: Represents a renter saving a property to their favorites. Idempotent — adding a duplicate returns the existing record (API handles this). Composite unique constraint prevents duplicates.\n220: \n221: **Table:** `favorites`\n222: \n223: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n224: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n225: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n226: | `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | The renter who favorited |\n227: | `property_id` | `uuid` | FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | The favorited property |\n228: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n229: \n230: **Indexes:**\n231: - `UNIQUE` on `(user_id, property_id)` — prevents duplicate favorites\n232: - `INDEX` on `user_id`\n233: - `INDEX` on `property_id`\n234: \n235: **Relationships:**\n236: - `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n237: - `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n241: ### Inquiry\n242: \n243: Represents a contact/inquiry submission from a renter about a specific property. Admins manage inquiry status and responses.\n244: \n245: **Table:** `inquiries`\n246: \n247: | Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n248: |-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n249: | `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n250: | `property_id` | `uuid` | FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE SET NULL | Subject property |\n251: | `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE SET NULL | Submitting renter |\n252: | `name` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | Submitter's name (denormalized for display) |\n253: | `email` | `varchar(255)` | NOT NULL | Submitter's email (denormalized) |\n254: | `phone` | `varchar(20)` | NULLABLE | Submitter's phone (denormalized) |\n255: | `message` | `text` | NOT NULL | Inquiry message body (10–2000 chars) |\n256: | `status` | `enum` (`InquiryStatusEnum`) | NOT NULL, default: `'new'` | `new` \\| `read` \\| `responded` |\n257: | `response` | `text` | NULLABLE | Admin's response text |\n258: | `responded_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Set when admin responds |\n259: | `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n260: | `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n261: \n262: **Note:** `name`, `email`, `phone` are denormalized from the `User` record at submission time. This preserves the inquiry even if the user account is later deleted (hence `ON DELETE SET NULL` on `user_id`).\n263: \n264: **Indexes:**\n265: - `INDEX` on `property_id`\n266: - `INDEX` on `user_id`\n267: - `INDEX` on `status`\n268: - `INDEX` on `(status, created_at)` — for admin dashboard filtering\n269: \n270: **Relationships:**\n271: - `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n272: - `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n273: \n274: ---\n275: \n276: ## Enums\n277: \n278: ### RoleEnum\n279: \n280: Used in `users.role`.\n281: \n282: | Value | Description |\n283: |-------|-------------|\n284: | `renter` | Standard user who browses and saves properties, submits inquiries |\n285: | `admin` | Administrator with full system access |\n286: \n287: ---\n288: \n289: ### UserStatusEnum\n290: \n291: Used in `users.status`.\n292: \n293: | Value | Description |\n294: |-------|-------------|\n295: | `active` | Account in good standing |\n296: | `suspended` | Account suspended by admin; cannot log in |\n297: \n298: ---\n299: \n300: ### PropertyTypeEnum\n301: \n302: Used in `properties.property_type`.\n303: \n304: | Value | Description |\n305: |-------|-------------|\n306: | `apartment` | Apartment unit |\n307: | `house` | Single-family house |\n308: | `condo` | Condominium |\n309: | `townhouse` | Townhouse |\n310: | `studio` | Studio apartment |\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ### InquiryStatusEnum\n315: \n316: Used in `inquiries.status`.\n317: \n318: | Value | Description |\n319: |-------|-------------|\n320: | `new` | Unread inquiry (default on submission) |\n321: | `read` | Viewed by admin |\n322: | `responded` | Admin has sent a response |\n323: \n324: ---\n325: \n326: ## Relationships\n327: \n328: ### Entity Relationship Diagram\n329: \n330: ```\n331: users (1) ────────< (many) refresh_tokens\n332: users (1) ────────< (many) password_reset_tokens\n333: users (1) ────────< (many) favorites\n334: users (1) ────────< (many) inquiries\n335: \n336: properties (1) ───< (many) property_photos\n337: properties (1) ───< (many) favorites\n338: properties (1) ───< (many) inquiries\n339: properties (many) >────< (many) amenities  [via property_amenities]\n340: ```\n341: \n342: ### Foreign Key Summary\n343: \n344: | Child Table | FK Column | Parent Table | On Delete |\n345: |-------------|----------|--------------|-----------|\n346: | `refresh_tokens` | `user_id` | `users.id` | CASCADE |\n347: | `password_reset_tokens` | `user_id` | `users.id` | CASCADE |\n348: | `property_photos` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | CASCADE |\n349: | `property_amenities` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | CASCADE |\n350: | `property_amenities` | `amenity_id` | `amenities.id` | CASCADE |\n351: | `favorites` | `user_id` | `users.id` | CASCADE |\n352: | `favorites` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | CASCADE |\n353: | `inquiries` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | SET NULL |\n354: | `inquiries` | `user_id` | `users.id` | SET NULL |\n355: \n356: ### Relationship Details\n357: \n358: | Relationship | Type | Owner | Inverse | Junction |\n359: |-------------|------|-------|---------|----------|\n360: | User → RefreshToken | One-to-Many | — | RefreshToken.user ↔ User.refreshTokens | — |\n361: | User → PasswordResetToken | One-to-Many | — | PasswordResetToken.user ↔ User.resetTokens | — |\n362: | User → Favorite | One-to-Many | — | Favorite.user ↔ User.favorites | — |\n363: | User → Inquiry | One-to-Many | — | Inquiry.user ↔ User.inquiries | — |\n364: | Property → PropertyPhoto | One-to-Many | — | PropertyPhoto.property ↔ Property.photos | — |\n365: | Property → Favorite | One-to-Many | — | Favorite.property ↔ Property.favorites | — |\n366: | Property → Inquiry | One-to-Many | — | Inquiry.property ↔ Property.inquiries | — |\n367: | Property ↔ Amenity | Many-to-Many | Property (JoinTable) | Property.amenities ↔ Amenity.properties | `property_amenities` |\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## Conventions\n372: \n373: ### Timestamps\n374: - All `timestamp` columns use `default: now()` for `created_at`.\n375: - `updated_at` is auto-managed by TypeORM (`@UpdateDateColumn`).\n376: - `deleted_at` is managed by TypeORM soft-delete (`@DeleteDateColumn`).\n377: \n378: ### Soft Delete\n379: - Enabled on: `users`, `properties`, `amenities`.\n380: - NOT enabled on: `refresh_tokens` (managed via `revoked_at` + `expires_at`), `password_reset_tokens` (managed via `expires_at` + `used_at`), `favorites` (hard delete on unfavorite), `inquiries` (retained indefinitely for audit), `property_photos` (hard delete on removal), `property_amenities` (junction – hard delete on unlink).\n381: \n382: ### Naming\n383: - **Tables**: `snake_case` plural (e.g., `property_photos`, `password_reset_tokens`)\n384: - **Columns**: `snake_case` (e.g., `user_id`, `property_type`, `address_city`)\n385: - **Enums**: PascalCase suffix `Enum` in TypeScript (e.g., `RoleEnum`, `PropertyTypeEnum`)\n386: \n387: ### Data Types\n388: - Monetary values: `decimal(10,2)` (supports prices up to $99,999,999.99)\n389: - Geo-coordinates: `decimal(10,7)` (sub-meter precision)\n390: - Percentages/ratios: `decimal(5,2)` if needed in future\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: *Generated: 2026-05-19 | Source: PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md + PROJECT_API.md + database-patterns.md*\n\n(End of file - total 394 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PROJECT_DATABASE\n\n## Schema Overview\n\nAll entities extend `BaseEntity` which provides:\n- `id` — UUID primary key\n- `createdAt` — `timestamp` (auto-managed)\n- `updatedAt` — `timestamp` (auto-managed)\n- `deletedAt` — `timestamp | null` (soft delete support)\n\nColumn naming convention: `snake_case` in the database (`@CreateDateColumn({ name: 'created_at' })`).\n\n---\n\n## Entities\n\n### User\n\nRepresents all registered users (Renters and Admins). Extends `BaseEntity` with soft delete.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md","time":{"start":1779168258256,"end":1779168258672}},"id":"prt_e3eb12348001DfUF7E5vsW3D7e","sessionID":"ses_1c14f16cdffegT7S1cr6CAFB7m","messageID":"msg_e3eb116bc001g3JyfqGUYJ6Nr2"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779168260347,"sessionID":"ses_1c14f16cdffegT7S1cr6CAFB7m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_ql9W9fXNmyRZ6BmyIaki4804","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/routing-and-controllers.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/routing-and-controllers.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Routing and Controllers - NestJS Best Practices\n2: \n3: Complete guide to NestJS controllers with BaseController pattern and decorators.\n4: \n5: ## Table of Contents\n6: \n7: - [NestJS Controllers Overview](#nestjs-controllers-overview)\n8: - [BaseController Pattern](#basecontroller-pattern)\n9: - [Route Decorators](#route-decorators)\n10: - [Custom Decorators](#custom-decorators)\n11: - [Good Examples](#good-examples)\n12: - [Anti-Patterns](#anti-patterns)\n13: - [Swagger Documentation](#swagger-documentation)\n14: - [Override Pattern](#override-pattern)\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## NestJS Controllers Overview\n19: \n20: ### The Golden Rule\n21: \n22: **Controllers should ONLY:**\n23: \n24: - ✅ Define routes with decorators (@Get, @Post, etc.)\n25: - ✅ Extract request data (@Param, @Body, @Query)\n26: - ✅ Delegate to services\n27: - ✅ Return responses (wrapped automatically)\n28: \n29: **Controllers should NEVER:**\n30: \n31: - ❌ Contain business logic\n32: - ❌ Access database directly (use services)\n33: - ❌ Handle complex validations (DTOs handle this)\n34: - ❌ Format responses manually (TransformInterceptor does this)\n35: \n36: ### Clean Controller Pattern\n37: \n38: ```typescript\n39: // src/modules/users/user.controller.ts\n40: import {\n41:     Controller,\n42:     Get,\n43:     Post,\n44:     Body,\n45:     Param,\n46:     ParseUUIDPipe,\n47: } from '@nestjs/common';\n48: import { ApiTags } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n49: import { BaseController } from 'src/core/base';\n50: import { ApiSwagger } from 'src/core/decorators';\n51: import { UserService } from './user.service';\n52: import { User } from './user.entity';\n53: import { CreateUserDto, UpdateUserDto } from './dtos';\n54: \n55: @ApiTags('Users')\n56: @Controller('users')\n57: export class UserController extends BaseController<\n58:     User,\n59:     CreateUserDto,\n60:     UpdateUserDto\n61: > {\n62:     constructor(private readonly userService: UserService) {\n63:         super(userService);\n64:     }\n65: \n66:     // All CRUD operations inherited automatically!\n67:     // - POST   /users\n68:     // - GET    /users\n69:     // - GET    /users/:id\n70:     // - PATCH  /users/:id\n71:     // - DELETE /users/:id\n72: }\n73: ```\n74: \n75: **Key Points:**\n76: \n77: - Extends BaseController for automatic CRUD\n78: - Decorator-based routing (@Get, @Post, etc.)\n79: - Type-safe with generics\n80: - Clean, readable, maintainable\n81: - All endpoints visible at a glance\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## BaseController Pattern\n86: \n87: ### Why BaseController?\n88: \n89: **Benefits:**\n90: \n91: - ✅ **90% less code** - Full CRUD automatically\n92: - ✅ **Consistent responses** - All wrapped in ResponsePayloadDto\n93: - ✅ **Automatic validation** - UUID validation on :id routes\n94: - ✅ **Swagger docs** - Auto-generated with @ApiSwagger\n95: - ✅ **Error handling** - Inherited from base\n96: - ✅ **Pagination support** - Built-in for GET /\n97: - ✅ **Type-safe** - Generic types throughout\n98: \n99: ### Inherited CRUD Operations\n100: \n101: When you extend BaseController, you automatically get:\n102: \n103: ```typescript\n104: @Post()\n105: @HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)\n106: @ApiSwagger({ resourceName: 'Resource', operation: 'create', successStatus: 201 })\n107: async create(@Body() createDto: CreateDto): Promise<CreatedResponseDto<T>>\n108: \n109: @Get()\n110: @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n111: @ApiSwagger({ resourceName: 'Resources', operation: 'getAll', isArray: true, withPagination: true })\n112: async findAll(@Query() paginationDto: PaginationDto): Promise<PaginatedResponseDto<T>>\n113: \n114: @Get(':id')\n115: @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n116: @ApiSwagger({ resourceName: 'Resource', operation: 'getOne' })\n117: async findOne(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string): Promise<SuccessResponseDto<T>>\n118: \n119: @Patch(':id')\n120: @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n121: @ApiSwagger({ resourceName: 'Resource', operation: 'update' })\n122: async update(\n123:     @Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string,\n124:     @Body() updateDto: UpdateDto\n125: ): Promise<UpdatedResponseDto<T>>\n126: \n127: @Delete(':id')\n128: @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n129: @ApiSwagger({ resourceName: 'Resource', operation: 'delete' })\n130: async remove(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string): Promise<DeletedResponseDto>\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ### Response Format\n134: \n135: All responses are automatically wrapped by TransformInterceptor:\n136: \n137: ```typescript\n138: {\n139:     \"success\": true,\n140:     \"statusCode\": 200,\n141:     \"message\": \"User retrieved successfully\",\n142:     \"data\": {\n143:         \"id\": \"uuid-here\",\n144:         \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n145:         \"name\": \"John Doe\",\n146:         \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T12:00:00.000Z\",\n147:         \"updatedAt\": \"2024-01-01T12:00:00.000Z\"\n148:     },\n149:     \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-01T12:00:00.000Z\",\n150:     \"path\": \"/api/users/uuid-here\"\n151: }\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ## Route Decorators\n157: \n158: ### HTTP Method Decorators\n159: \n160: ```typescript\n161: import {\n162:     Get,\n163:     Post,\n164:     Put,\n165:     Patch,\n166:     Delete,\n167:     HttpCode,\n168:     HttpStatus,\n169: } from '@nestjs/common';\n170: \n171: @Controller('users')\n172: export class UserController {\n173:     @Get() // GET /users\n174:     @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK) // 200\n175:     findAll() {}\n176: \n177:     @Get(':id') // GET /users/:id\n178:     findOne(@Param('id') id: string) {}\n179: \n180:     @Post() // POST /users\n181:     @HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED) // 201\n182:     create(@Body() dto: CreateDto) {}\n183: \n184:     @Patch(':id') // PATCH /users/:id\n185:     update(@Param('id') id: string, @Body() dto: UpdateDto) {}\n186: \n187:     @Delete(':id') // DELETE /users/:id\n188:     remove(@Param('id') id: string) {}\n189: }\n190: ```\n191: \n192: ### Parameter Decorators\n193: \n194: ```typescript\n195: import { Param, Body, Query, Headers, Req, Res } from '@nestjs/common';\n196: \n197: @Controller('users')\n198: export class UserController {\n199:     @Get(':id')\n200:     findOne(\n201:         @Param('id') id: string, // Route parameter\n202:         @Query('include') include?: string, // Query parameter\n203:         @Headers('authorization') auth?: string, // Header\n204:     ) {}\n205: \n206:     @Post()\n207:     create(\n208:         @Body() createDto: CreateUserDto, // Request body\n209:     ) {}\n210: \n211:     @Get()\n212:     findAll(\n213:         @Query() query: PaginationDto, // All query params as DTO\n214:     ) {}\n215: }\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ### Validation Pipes\n219: \n220: ```typescript\n221: import { ParseUUIDPipe, ParseIntPipe, ValidationPipe } from '@nestjs/common';\n222: \n223: @Controller('users')\n224: export class UserController {\n225:     @Get(':id')\n226:     findOne(\n227:         @Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string, // Auto-validate UUID\n228:     ) {}\n229: \n230:     @Get()\n231:     findAll(\n232:         @Query('page', ParseIntPipe) page: number, // Auto-parse to integer\n233:     ) {}\n234: \n235:     @Post()\n236:     create(\n237:         @Body() dto: CreateUserDto, // ValidationPipe runs globally\n238:     ) {}\n239: }\n240: ```\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ## Custom Decorators\n245: \n246: ### @Public() - Bypass Authentication\n247: \n248: ```typescript\n249: import { Public } from 'src/core/decorators';\n250: \n251: @Controller('users')\n252: export class UserController {\n253:     @Public() // This route doesn't require authentication\n254:     @Post()\n255:     async create(@Body() createUserDto: CreateUserDto) {\n256:         return await this.userService.createUser(createUserDto);\n257:     }\n258: \n259:     @Get(':id') // This route requires authentication (default)\n260:     async findOne(@Param('id') id: string) {\n261:         return await this.userService.findById(id);\n262:     }\n263: }\n264: ```\n265: \n266: ### @Roles() - Role-Based Access Control\n267: \n268: ```typescript\n269: import { Roles } from 'src/core/decorators';\n270: \n271: @Controller('users')\n272: export class UserController {\n273:     @Roles('admin') // Only admins can access\n274:     @Delete(':id')\n275:     async remove(@Param('id') id: string) {\n276:         return await this.userService.remove(id);\n277:     }\n278: \n279:     @Roles('admin', 'operations') // Multiple roles\n280:     @Patch(':id')\n281:     async update(@Param('id') id: string, @Body() dto: UpdateUserDto) {\n282:         return await this.userService.update(id, dto);\n283:     }\n284: }\n285: ```\n286: \n287: ### @CurrentUser() - Get Authenticated User\n288: \n289: ```typescript\n290: import { CurrentUser } from 'src/core/decorators';\n291: import { IJwtPayload } from '@shared/interfaces';\n292: \n293: @Controller('profile')\n294: export class ProfileController {\n295:     @Get()\n296:     async getProfile(@CurrentUser() user: IJwtPayload) {\n297:         // user contains: { userId, email, roles, ... }\n298:         return await this.userService.findById(user.userId);\n299:     }\n300: \n301:     @Patch()\n302:     async updateProfile(\n303:         @CurrentUser() user: IJwtPayload,\n304:         @Body() dto: UpdateProfileDto,\n305:     ) {\n306:         return await this.userService.update(user.userId, dto);\n307:     }\n308: }\n309: ```\n310: \n311: ### @ApiSwagger() - Swagger Documentation\n312: \n313: ```typescript\n314: import { ApiSwagger } from 'src/core/decorators';\n315: \n316: @Controller('users')\n317: export class UserController {\n318:     @Post()\n319:     @ApiSwagger({\n320:         resourceName: 'User',\n321:         operation: 'create',\n322:         requestDto: CreateUserDto,\n323:         responseDto: UserResponseDto,\n324:         successStatus: 201,\n325:         errors: [\n326:             { status: 400, description: 'Invalid input data' },\n327:             { status: 409, description: 'Email already exists' },\n328:         ],\n329:     })\n330:     async create(@Body() dto: CreateUserDto) {\n331:         return await this.userService.create(dto);\n332:     }\n333: }\n334: ```\n335: \n336: ---\n337: \n338: ## Good Examples\n339: \n340: ### Example 1: User Controller (Excellent ✅)\n341: \n342: **File:** `src/modules/users/user.controller.ts`\n343: \n344: ```typescript\n345: import {\n346:     Controller,\n347:     Get,\n348:     Post,\n349:     Body,\n350:     Patch,\n351:     Param,\n352:     Query,\n353:     Delete,\n354:     HttpCode,\n355:     HttpStatus,\n356:     ParseUUIDPipe,\n357: } from '@nestjs/common';\n358: import { ApiTags } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n359: import { BaseController } from 'src/core/base';\n360: import { ApiSwagger, Public } from 'src/core/decorators';\n361: import { ResponsePayloadDto } from '@shared/dtos';\n362: import { UserService } from './user.service';\n363: import { CreateUserDto, UpdateUserDto, UserResponseDto } from './dtos';\n364: import { User } from './user.entity';\n365: \n366: @ApiTags('Users')\n367: @Controller('users')\n368: export class UserController extends BaseController<\n369:     User,\n370:     CreateUserDto,\n371:     UpdateUserDto\n372: > {\n373:     constructor(private readonly userService: UserService) {\n374:         super(userService);\n375:     }\n376: \n377:     // Override create to make it public and use custom service method\n378:     @Public()\n379:     @Post()\n380:     @HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)\n381:     @ApiSwagger({\n382:         resourceName: 'User',\n383:         operation: 'create',\n384:         requestDto: CreateUserDto,\n385:         responseDto: UserResponseDto,\n386:         successStatus: 201,\n387:         errors: [\n388:             { status: 400, description: 'Invalid input data' },\n389:             { status: 409, description: 'User with this email already exists' },\n390:         ],\n391:     })\n392:     async create(\n393:         @Body() createUserDto: CreateUserDto,\n394:     ): Promise<ResponsePayloadDto<User>> {\n395:         return await this.userService.createUser(createUserDto);\n396:     }\n397: \n398:     // Custom endpoint: Get active users\n399:     @Get('active')\n400:     @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n401:     @ApiSwagger({\n402:         resourceName: 'Active Users',\n403:         operation: 'getAll',\n404:         responseDto: UserResponseDto,\n405:         isArray: true,\n406:     })\n407:     async getActiveUsers() {\n408:         return this.userService.getActiveUsers();\n409:     }\n410: \n411:     // Custom endpoint: Search by email\n412:     @Get('search')\n413:     @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n414:     @ApiSwagger({\n415:         resourceName: 'Users',\n416:         operation: 'search',\n417:         summary: 'Search users by email',\n418:         responseDto: UserResponseDto,\n419:         isArray: true,\n420:     })\n421:     async searchByEmail(@Query('email') email: string) {\n422:         if (!email) return [];\n423:         const user = await this.userService.findByEmail(email);\n424:         return user ? [user] : [];\n425:     }\n426: \n427:     // Inherited CRUD endpoints:\n428:     // - GET /users (with pagination)\n429:     // - GET /users/:id\n430:     // - PATCH /users/:id\n431:     // - DELETE /users/:id\n432: }\n433: ```\n434: \n435: **What Makes This Excellent:**\n436: \n437: - ✅ Extends BaseController for automatic CRUD\n438: - ✅ Custom endpoints added where needed\n439: - ✅ Proper use of @Public decorator\n440: - ✅ Complete Swagger documentation\n441: - ✅ Clean parameter extraction\n442: - ✅ Zero business logic\n443: \n444: ### Example 2: Authentication Controller (Good ✅)\n445: \n446: **File:** `src/modules/auth/auth.controller.ts`\n447: \n448: ```typescript\n449: import {\n450:     Body,\n451:     Controller,\n452:     Get,\n453:     Post,\n454:     UseGuards,\n455:     UseInterceptors,\n456: } from '@nestjs/common';\n457: import { ApiTags } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n458: import { AuthService } from './auth.service';\n459: import { LoginDto, SocialLoginDto } from './dtos';\n460: import { ApiSwagger, CurrentUser, Public } from '@core/decorators';\n461: import { JwtAuthGuard } from '@core/guards';\n462: import { SetToken, RemoveToken } from '@core/interceptors';\n463: import { IJwtPayload } from '@shared/interfaces';\n464: import { LoginResponsePayloadDto, ResponsePayloadDto } from '@shared/dtos';\n465: \n466: @ApiTags('Authentication')\n467: @Controller('auth')\n468: export class AuthController {\n469:     constructor(private authService: AuthService) {}\n470: \n471:     @Post('login')\n472:     @Public()\n473:     @UseInterceptors(SetToken)\n474:     @ApiSwagger({\n475:         resourceName: 'Login',\n476:         operation: 'custom',\n477:         summary: 'User login',\n478:         requestDto: LoginDto,\n479:         responseDto: LoginResponsePayloadDto,\n480:         requiresAuth: false,\n481:         errors: [{ status: 401, description: 'Incorrect email or password' }],\n482:     })\n483:     async login(\n484:         @Body() dto: LoginDto,\n485:     ): Promise<ResponsePayloadDto<LoginResponsePayloadDto>> {\n486:         return await this.authService.login(dto);\n487:     }\n488: \n489:     @Post('social-login')\n490:     @Public()\n491:     @UseInterceptors(SetToken)\n492:     @ApiSwagger({\n493:         resourceName: 'Social Login',\n494:         operation: 'custom',\n495:         summary: 'Social login (Google, Kakao, Naver)',\n496:         requestDto: SocialLoginDto,\n497:         responseDto: LoginResponsePayloadDto,\n498:         requiresAuth: false,\n499:     })\n500:     async socialLogin(\n501:         @Body() dto: SocialLoginDto,\n502:     ): Promise<LoginResponsePayloadDto> {\n503:         return await this.authService.socialLogin(dto);\n504:     }\n505: \n506:     @Get('check-login')\n507:     @UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)\n508:     @ApiSwagger({\n509:         resourceName: 'Check Login',\n510:         operation: 'custom',\n511:         summary: 'Check if user is logged in',\n512:         responseDto: LoginResponsePayloadDto,\n513:         requiresAuth: true,\n514:     })\n515:     async checkUserLogin(@CurrentUser() user: IJwtPayload | null) {\n516:         if (user) {\n517:             return await this.authService.getUserInformation(user);\n518:         }\n519:         return null;\n520:     }\n521: \n522:     @Get('logout')\n523:     @UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)\n524:     @UseInterceptors(RemoveToken)\n525:     @ApiSwagger({\n526:         resourceName: 'Logout',\n527:         operation: 'custom',\n528:         summary: 'Logout user',\n529:         requiresAuth: true,\n530:     })\n531:     async logout(@CurrentUser() user: IJwtPayload | null) {\n532:         return await this.authService.logout(user);\n533:     }\n534: }\n535: ```\n536: \n537: **What Makes This Good:**\n538: \n539: - ✅ Clear route definitions\n540: - ✅ Proper use of @Public decorator\n541: - ✅ Interceptors for token management\n542: - ✅ @CurrentUser decorator for auth\n543: - ✅ Complete Swagger documentation\n544: - ✅ All logic delegated to service\n545: \n546: ---\n547: \n548: ## Anti-Patterns\n549: \n550: ### Anti-Pattern 1: Business Logic in Controller (Bad ❌)\n551: \n552: ```typescript\n553: // ❌ ANTI-PATTERN: Business logic in controller\n554: @Post()\n555: async create(@Body() createUserDto: CreateUserDto) {\n556:     // ❌ Email validation in controller\n557:     const emailRegex = /^[^\\s@]+@[^\\s@]+\\.[^\\s@]+$/;\n558:     if (!emailRegex.test(createUserDto.email)) {\n559:         throw new BadRequestException('Invalid email format');\n560:     }\n561: \n562:     // ❌ Business rule checking in controller\n563:     const existing = await this.userService.findByEmail(createUserDto.email);\n564:     if (existing) {\n565:         throw new ConflictException('Email already exists');\n566:     }\n567: \n568:     // ❌ Data transformation in controller\n569:     const hashedPassword = await bcrypt.hash(createUserDto.password, 10);\n570:     const userData = {\n571:         ...createUserDto,\n572:         password: hashedPassword,\n573:         isActive: true,\n574:     };\n575: \n576:     // Finally create user\n577:     return await this.userService.create(userData);\n578: }\n579: ```\n580: \n581: **Why This Is Terrible:**\n582: \n583: - Violates single responsibility principle\n584: - Business logic not reusable\n585: - Hard to test\n586: - Mixes HTTP concerns with business rules\n587: \n588: **How to Fix:**\n589: \n590: ```typescript\n591: // ✅ GOOD: Delegate to service\n592: @Post()\n593: async create(@Body() createUserDto: CreateUserDto) {\n594:     return await this.userService.createUser(createUserDto);\n595: }\n596: \n597: // Service handles all business logic:\n598: // - Email validation (via DTO with class-validator)\n599: // - Duplicate checking\n600: // - Password hashing\n601: // - Setting defaults\n602: ```\n603: \n604: ### Anti-Pattern 2: Not Using BaseController (Bad ❌)\n605: \n606: ```typescript\n607: // ❌ ANTI-PATTERN: Reimplementing CRUD manually\n608: @Controller('products')\n609: export class ProductController {\n610:     constructor(private productService: ProductService) {}\n611: \n612:     @Post()\n613:     async create(@Body() dto: CreateProductDto) {\n614:         try {\n615:             const product = await this.productService.create(dto);\n616:             return {\n617:                 success: true,\n618:                 statusCode: 201,\n619:                 message: 'Product created',\n620:                 data: product,\n621:             };\n622:         } catch (error) {\n623:             throw new InternalServerErrorException('Failed to create product');\n624:         }\n625:     }\n626: \n627:     @Get()\n628:     async findAll(@Query('page') page = 1, @Query('limit') limit = 10) {\n629:         const products = await this.productService.findAll();\n630:         // Manual pagination logic...\n631:         return {\n632:             success: true,\n633:             data: products,\n634:             page,\n635:             limit,\n636:         };\n637:     }\n638: \n639:     // ... 200 more lines of manual CRUD\n640: }\n641: ```\n642: \n643: **How to Fix:**\n644: \n645: ```typescript\n646: // ✅ GOOD: Use BaseController\n647: @ApiTags('Products')\n648: @Controller('products')\n649: export class ProductController extends BaseController<\n650:     Product,\n651:     CreateProductDto,\n652:     UpdateProductDto\n653: > {\n654:     constructor(private readonly productService: ProductService) {\n655:         super(productService);\n656:     }\n657: \n658:     // All CRUD operations inherited!\n659:     // Only add custom endpoints if needed\n660: }\n661: ```\n662: \n663: ---\n664: \n665: ## Swagger Documentation\n666: \n667: ### Complete Swagger Example\n668: \n669: ```typescript\n670: import {\n671:     ApiTags,\n672:     ApiOperation,\n673:     ApiResponse,\n674:     ApiBearerAuth,\n675: } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n676: import { ApiSwagger } from 'src/core/decorators';\n677: \n678: @ApiTags('Users')\n679: @ApiBearerAuth() // Requires authentication by default\n680: @Controller('users')\n681: export class UserController extends BaseController<\n682:     User,\n683:     CreateUserDto,\n684:     UpdateUserDto\n685: > {\n686:     constructor(private readonly userService: UserService) {\n687:         super(userService);\n688:     }\n689: \n690:     @Post()\n691:     @ApiSwagger({\n692:         resourceName: 'User',\n693:         operation: 'create',\n694:         requestDto: CreateUserDto,\n695:         responseDto: UserResponseDto,\n696:         successStatus: 201,\n697:         errors: [\n698:             { status: 400, description: 'Invalid input data' },\n699:             { status: 409, description: 'User already exists' },\n700:         ],\n701:     })\n702:     async create(@Body() dto: CreateUserDto) {\n703:         return await this.userService.create(dto);\n704:     }\n705: \n706:     // Or use standard NestJS decorators:\n707:     @Get(':id')\n708:     @ApiOperation({ summary: 'Get user by ID' })\n709:     @ApiResponse({\n710:         status: 200,\n711:         description: 'User found',\n712:         type: UserResponseDto,\n713:     })\n714:     @ApiResponse({ status: 404, description: 'User not found' })\n715:     async findOne(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string) {\n716:         return await this.userService.findById(id);\n717:     }\n718: }\n719: ```\n720: \n721: ### Swagger DTO Example\n722: \n723: ```typescript\n724: import { ApiProperty } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n725: import { IsEmail, IsString, MinLength, MaxLength } from 'class-validator';\n726: \n727: export class CreateUserDto {\n728:     @ApiProperty({\n729:         example: 'user@example.com',\n730:         description: 'User email address',\n731:     })\n732:     @IsEmail()\n733:     email: string;\n734: \n735:     @ApiProperty({\n736:         example: 'John Doe',\n737:         description: 'User full name',\n738:         minLength: 2,\n739:         maxLength: 100,\n740:     })\n741:     @IsString()\n742:     @MinLength(2)\n743:     @MaxLength(100)\n744:     name: string;\n745: \n746:     @ApiProperty({\n747:         example: 'SecurePassword123',\n748:         description: 'User password',\n749:         minLength: 8,\n750:     })\n751:     @IsString()\n752:     @MinLength(8)\n753:     password: string;\n754: }\n755: ```\n756: \n757: ---\n758: \n759: ## Override Pattern\n760: \n761: ### When to Override BaseController Methods\n762: \n763: Override inherited methods when you need:\n764: \n765: - Custom business logic\n766: - Different response format\n767: - Additional validation\n768: - Custom error handling\n769: - Integration with other services\n770: \n771: ### Override Example\n772: \n773: ```typescript\n774: @ApiTags('Users')\n775: @Controller('users')\n776: export class UserController extends BaseController<\n777:     User,\n778:     CreateUserDto,\n779:     UpdateUserDto\n780: > {\n781:     constructor(\n782:         private readonly userService: UserService,\n783:         private readonly mailService: MailService,\n784:     ) {\n785:         super(userService);\n786:     }\n787: \n788:     // Override create to add email notification\n789:     @Public()\n790:     @Post()\n791:     @HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)\n792:     @ApiSwagger({\n793:         resourceName: 'User',\n794:         operation: 'create',\n795:         responseDto: UserResponseDto,\n796:     })\n797:     async create(\n798:         @Body() createUserDto: CreateUserDto,\n799:     ): Promise<ResponsePayloadDto<User>> {\n800:         // Create user\n801:         const result = await this.userService.createUser(createUserDto);\n802: \n803:         // Send welcome email (custom logic)\n804:         await this.mailService.sendWelcome(createUserDto.email);\n805: \n806:         return result;\n807:     }\n808: \n809:     // Override update to add logging\n810:     @Patch(':id')\n811:     @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n812:     @ApiSwagger({\n813:         resourceName: 'User',\n814:         operation: 'update',\n815:         responseDto: UserResponseDto,\n816:     })\n817:     async update(\n818:         @Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string,\n819:         @Body() updateUserDto: UpdateUserDto,\n820:         @CurrentUser() user: IJwtPayload,\n821:     ): Promise<ResponsePayloadDto<User>> {\n822:         // Update user\n823:         const updatedUser = await this.userService.updateUser(\n824:             id,\n825:             updateUserDto,\n826:         );\n827: \n828:         // Log action\n829:         console.log(`User ${user.userId} updated user ${id}`);\n830: \n831:         return new ResponsePayloadDto({\n832:             success: true,\n833:             statusCode: 200,\n834:             message: 'User updated successfully',\n835:             data: updatedUser,\n836:             timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n837:         });\n838:     }\n839: \n840:     // Keep other CRUD operations from BaseController:\n841:     // - findAll (GET /)\n842:     // - findOne (GET /:id)\n843:     // - remove (DELETE /:id)\n844: }\n845: ```\n846: \n847: ---\n848: \n849: ## Best Practices Summary\n850: \n851: ### ✅ DO:\n852: \n853: - Extend BaseController for all CRUD endpoints\n854: - Use NestJS decorators (@Get, @Post, @Body, @Param)\n855: - Use custom decorators (@Public, @Roles, @CurrentUser)\n856: - Add @ApiSwagger for documentation\n857: - Delegate all logic to services\n858: - Override base methods only when necessary\n859: - Use ParseUUIDPipe for ID validation\n860: - Return DTOs from methods\n861: \n862: ### ❌ DON'T:\n863: \n864: - Put business logic in controllers\n865: - Access database directly\n866: - Handle complex validations (use DTOs)\n867: - Format responses manually (interceptor does this)\n868: - Use process.env directly\n869: - Implement CRUD manually (use BaseController)\n870: - Forget @ApiTags decorator\n871: - Mix HTTP concerns with business rules\n872: \n873: ---\n874: \n875: ---\n876: \n877: ## MANDATORY: Controller Rules (from Base Architecture)\n878: \n879: ### Controller Size Limit: 200 Lines\n880: \n881: If a controller exceeds 200 lines, split into sub-controllers by feature area:\n882: - `UserController` (CRUD) + `UserProfileController` (profile-specific)\n883: - `OrderController` (CRUD) + `OrderPaymentController` (payment-specific)\n884: \n885: ### Swagger on EVERY Method\n886: \n887: ```typescript\n888: @ApiOperation({ summary: 'Get user by ID' })\n889: @ApiResponse({ status: 200, description: 'User found', type: UserResponseDto })\n890: @ApiResponse({ status: 404, description: 'User not found' })\n891: @Get(':id')\n892: findOne(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string) {\n893:   return this.userService.findOne(id);\n894: }\n895: ```\n896: \n897: No controller method without `@ApiOperation` and at least one `@ApiResponse`.\n898: \n899: ### Rate Limiting on Public Endpoints\n900: \n901: ```typescript\n902: import { Throttle } from '@nestjs/throttler';\n903: \n904: @Public()\n905: @Throttle({ default: { limit: 10, ttl: 60000 } })\n906: @Post('login')\n907: login(@Body() dto: LoginDto) { ... }\n908: ```\n909: \n910: Apply to: login, register, forgot-password, verify-email, resend-verification.\n911: \n912: ### Proper HTTP Status Codes\n913: \n914: | Operation | Status | Decorator |\n915: |-----------|--------|-----------|\n916: | Create | 201 | `@HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)` |\n917: | Update | 200 | (default) |\n918: | Delete | 204 | `@HttpCode(HttpStatus.NO_CONTENT)` |\n919: | List | 200 | (default) |\n920: | Not Found | 404 | Throw `NotFoundException` from service |\n921: \n922: ---\n923: \n924: **Related Files:**\n925: \n926: - [SKILL.md](../SKILL.md) - Main guide\n927: - [architecture-overview.md](architecture-overview.md) - Four-layer architecture\n928: - [services-and-repositories.md](services-and-repositories.md) - Service layer patterns\n929: - [validation-patterns.md](validation-patterns.md) - DTO validation\n\n(End of file - total 929 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Routing and Controllers - NestJS Best Practices\n\nComplete guide to NestJS controllers with BaseController pattern and decorators.\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n- [NestJS Controllers Overview](#nestjs-controllers-overview)\n- [BaseController Pattern](#basecontroller-pattern)\n- [Route Decorators](#route-decorators)\n- [Custom Decorators](#custom-decorators)\n- [Good Examples](#good-examples)\n- [Anti-Patterns](#anti-patterns)\n- [Swagger Documentation](#swagger-documentation)\n- [Override Pattern](#override-pattern)\n\n---\n\n## NestJS Controllers Overview\n\n### The Golden Rule","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/nestjs/guides/routing-and-controllers.md","time":{"start":1779168259965,"end":1779168260344}},"id":"prt_e3eb12a69001osemb30FJpmprt","sessionID":"ses_1c14f16cdffegT7S1cr6CAFB7m","messageID":"msg_e3eb116bc001g3JyfqGUYJ6Nr2"}}
